<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>MUFASA — Guides</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Anton&family=Barlow+Condensed:wght@300;400;600;700&family=Barlow:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root{
  --g:#D4942A;--gl:#F0B84A;--gd:#A8741F;
  --gdim:rgba(212,148,42,.2);--gfaint:rgba(212,148,42,.06);
  --bg:#050403;--s1:#0C0A08;--s2:#121008;
  --card:#18150F;--card2:#1F1B12;
  --b1:rgba(212,148,42,.13);--b2:rgba(212,148,42,.32);
  --w:#F4EFE4;--grey:#A09890;--dim:#7A7570;
  --r:6px;--r2:12px;--r3:20px;
}
*,*::before,*::after{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box;}
html{scroll-behavior:smooth;}
body{font-family:'Barlow',sans-serif;background:var(--bg);color:var(--w);min-height:100vh;overflow-x:hidden;}
::-webkit-scrollbar{width:3px;}
::-webkit-scrollbar-track{background:var(--s1);}
::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb{background:var(--b2);border-radius:2px;}

/* ── PAGE WRAPPER ── */
.guides-wrap{padding:28px 5vw 60px;max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;}

/* ── HEADER ── */
.guides-header{margin-bottom:26px;}
.stag{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-size:.72rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.3em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--g);margin-bottom:6px;}
.sh{font-family:'Anton',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(1.8rem,5vw,2.8rem);line-height:1;color:var(--w);margin-bottom:6px;}
.ssub{font-size:.88rem;color:var(--grey);line-height:1.6;}

/* ── DAILY TIP BANNER ── */
.tip-banner{
  background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--card),var(--card2));
  border:1px solid var(--b2);
  border-left:3px solid var(--g);
  border-radius:var(--r2);
  padding:14px 18px;
  margin-bottom:28px;
  display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;
  animation:tipIn .5s ease both;
}
@keyframes tipIn{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(-8px);}to{opacity:1;transform:none;}}
.tip-icon{font-size:1.3rem;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;}
.tip-body{}
.tip-label{font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-size:.65rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.28em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--g);margin-bottom:3px;}
.tip-text{font-size:.86rem;color:var(--w);line-height:1.55;}
.tip-refresh{background:none;border:none;color:var(--dim);font-size:.75rem;cursor:pointer;margin-top:5px;font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;transition:color .2s;padding:0;}
.tip-refresh:hover{color:var(--g);}

/* ── GOAL SELECTOR ── */
.goal-bar{
  display:flex;gap:7px;flex-wrap:wrap;
  margin-bottom:26px;
  padding:16px 18px;
  background:var(--s1);
  border:1px solid var(--b1);
  border-radius:var(--r2);
}
.goal-bar-label{
  font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-size:.72rem;
  font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:var(--grey);width:100%;margin-bottom:5px;
}
.gbtn{
  background:none;border:1px solid var(--b1);
  color:var(--grey);padding:7px 16px;
  border-radius:20px;
  font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;font-size:.78rem;font-weight:700;
  letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;
  cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;
}
.gbtn:hover{border-color:var(--g);color:var(--g);background:var(--gfaint);}
.gbtn.on{background:var(--g);border-color:var(--g);color:var(--bg);}

/* ── GUIDE CARDS ── */
.glist{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:10px;}

.gitem{
  background:var(--card);
  border:1px solid var(--b1);
  border-radius:var(--r2);
  overflow:hidden;
  transition:border-color .3s;
}
.gitem.open{border-color:var(--b2);}

/* header row */
.ghd{
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;
  padding:18px 20px;cursor:pointer;
  transition:background .2s;
  user-select:none;
}
.ghd:hover{background:var(--gfaint);}
.ghd-ic{
  width:44px;height:44px;
  border-radius:var(--r2);
  background:var(--gdim);
  border:1px solid var(--b2);
  display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
  font-size:1.35rem;flex-shrink:0;
  transition:background .3s;
}
.gitem.open .ghd-ic{background:var(--g);}
.ghd-info{flex:1;}
.ghd-t{
  font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;
  font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.04em;
  color:var(--w);
}
.ghd-s{font-size:.76rem;color:var(--grey);margin-top:3px;}
.garr{
  color:var(--grey);font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;
  transition:transform .3s,color .3s;
  flex-shrink:0;
}
.gitem.open .garr{transform:rotate(90deg);color:var(--g);}

/* collapsible body */
.gbody{
  max-height:0;overflow:hidden;
  transition:max-height .45s cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1);
}
.gitem.open .gbody{max-height:4000px;}

/* inner content */
.gcont{padding:0 20px 20px;}
.gcont-divider{height:1px;background:var(--b1);margin-bottom:18px;}

/* sub-topic blocks */
.gsub{margin-bottom:18px;}
.gsub:last-child{margin-bottom:0;}
.gsub-hd{
  font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;
  font-size:.78rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.18em;
  text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--g);
  margin-bottom:9px;
  display:flex;align-items:center;gap:7px;
}
.gsub-hd::before{
  content:'';width:3px;height:13px;
  background:var(--g);border-radius:2px;flex-shrink:0;
}
.gsub ul{list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;}
.gsub ul li{
  font-size:.85rem;color:var(--grey);
  padding:7px 10px 7px 30px;
  position:relative;line-height:1.6;
  background:var(--s1);
  border-radius:var(--r);
  border-left:2px solid transparent;
  transition:border-color .2s,color .2s;
}
.gsub ul li:hover{border-left-color:var(--g);color:var(--w);}
.gsub ul li::before{
  content:'→';position:absolute;left:10px;
  color:var(--g);font-size:.8rem;
}

/* goal badge inside card */
.goal-badge{
  display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:5px;
  background:var(--gdim);border:1px solid var(--b2);
  border-radius:20px;padding:4px 11px;
  font-family:'Barlow Condensed',sans-serif;
  font-size:.68rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.15em;
  text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--gl);
  margin-bottom:14px;
}

/* highlight box */
.ghighlight{
  background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(212,148,42,.08),rgba(212,148,42,.03));
  border:1px solid var(--b2);
  border-radius:var(--r2);
  padding:14px 16px;
  margin-bottom:18px;
  font-size:.84rem;color:var(--w);
  line-height:1.6;
}
.ghighlight strong{color:var(--gl);}

/* ── FOOTER NOTE ── */
.guides-footer{
  margin-top:32px;
  padding:16px 18px;
  background:var(--s1);
  border:1px solid var(--b1);
  border-radius:var(--r2);
  font-size:.78rem;color:var(--dim);
  line-height:1.6;text-align:center;
}
.guides-footer span{color:var(--g);}

/* ── ANIMATIONS ── */
.fade-in{animation:fadeIn .4s ease both;}
@keyframes fadeIn{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(10px);}to{opacity:1;transform:none;}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="guides-wrap">

  <!-- HEADER -->
  <div class="guides-header fade-in">
    <div class="stag">Expert Knowledge</div>
    <h1 class="sh">EXPERT GUIDES</h1>
    <p class="ssub">Personalised advice. No fluff. Just what works for your goal.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- DAILY TIP -->
  <div class="tip-banner fade-in" id="tipBanner">
    <div class="tip-icon">💡</div>
    <div class="tip-body">
      <div class="tip-label">Tip of the Day</div>
      <div class="tip-text" id="tipText">Loading...</div>
      <button class="tip-refresh" onclick="nextTip()">↻ Next tip</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- GOAL SELECTOR -->
  <div class="goal-bar fade-in">
    <div class="goal-bar-label">Your Goal — select to personalise:</div>
    <button class="gbtn on" onclick="setGoal('muscle',this)">💪 Muscle Gain</button>
    <button class="gbtn" onclick="setGoal('fatloss',this)">🔥 Fat Loss</button>
    <button class="gbtn" onclick="setGoal('maintenance',this)">⚖️ Maintenance</button>
    <button class="gbtn" onclick="setGoal('beginner',this)">🌱 Complete Beginner</button>
  </div>

  <!-- GUIDE CARDS -->
  <div class="glist" id="guideList"></div>

  <!-- FOOTER -->
  <div class="guides-footer">
    <span>MUFASA STRENGTH</span> — All advice is based on evidence-backed fitness principles. Results depend on consistency, sleep, and nutrition working together.
  </div>

</div>

<script>
// ══════════════════════════════════════════
//  DAILY TIPS
// ══════════════════════════════════════════
const TIPS = [
  { icon:'💧', text:'Drink 500ml of water before your first meal. Hydration improves performance and reduces hunger.' },
  { icon:'🥚', text:'Eggs are the most complete protein source available in Kenya. 3 eggs = 18g of quality protein for under KSH 60.' },
  { icon:'😴', text:'One extra hour of sleep does more for muscle growth than an extra hour in the gym. Prioritise it.' },
  { icon:'⏱️', text:'Rest 60–90 seconds between sets for hypertrophy. Under 60s burns more calories. Over 2 min builds more strength.' },
  { icon:'📈', text:'If you hit the top of your rep range with good form, increase weight next session. That is progressive overload.' },
  { icon:'🍠', text:'Sweet potato is Kenya\'s best pre-workout carb. Slow digesting, cheap, and packed with potassium.' },
  { icon:'🦵', text:'Never skip legs. Lower body training releases more testosterone than any upper body movement.' },
  { icon:'🧂', text:'Add a pinch of salt to your water on heavy training days. Electrolytes prevent cramps and fatigue.' },
  { icon:'🔄', text:'Compound movements first, isolation last. Squats before leg curls. Press before lateral raises.' },
  { icon:'📓', text:'People who log their workouts progress 30% faster than those who don\'t. Use your phone notes at minimum.' },
  { icon:'🌅', text:'Morning training raises cortisol naturally with the day — good for fat burning. Evening training suits strength peak.' },
  { icon:'🫀', text:'10 minutes of skipping rope burns the same calories as 20 minutes of jogging. Cheapest cardio tool available.' },
  { icon:'🥩', text:'Protein goal simplified: eat your bodyweight in grams per day. 70kg = 70g protein minimum.' },
  { icon:'🧘', text:'5 minutes of deep breathing after training lowers cortisol and speeds up recovery. Not soft — strategic.' },
  { icon:'🍳', text:'Ugali + beans + sukuma wiki is one of the most complete muscle-building meals available. No supplements needed.' },
];

let tipIndex = new Date().getDay() % TIPS.length;

function renderTip() {
  const t = TIPS[tipIndex];
  document.getElementById('tipText').textContent = t.text;
  document.querySelector('.tip-icon').textContent = t.icon;
}

function nextTip() {
  tipIndex = (tipIndex + 1) % TIPS.length;
  renderTip();
}

// ══════════════════════════════════════════
//  GOAL STATE
// ══════════════════════════════════════════
let currentGoal = 'muscle';

function setGoal(goal, btn) {
  currentGoal = goal;
  document.querySelectorAll('.gbtn').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('on'));
  btn.classList.add('on');
  renderGuides();
}

// ══════════════════════════════════════════
//  GUIDES DATA (personalised by goal)
// ══════════════════════════════════════════
const GOAL_LABELS = {
  muscle:      '💪 Muscle Gain',
  fatloss:     '🔥 Fat Loss',
  maintenance: '⚖️ Maintenance',
  beginner:    '🌱 Complete Beginner',
};

const GOAL_HIGHLIGHTS = {
  nutrition: {
    muscle:      '<strong>Priority:</strong> Eat in a caloric surplus of 200–400 kcal/day. Protein is non-negotiable at 1.6–2g per kg of bodyweight.',
    fatloss:     '<strong>Priority:</strong> Eat in a 300–500 kcal deficit daily. Keep protein high (1.8–2.2g/kg) to preserve muscle while losing fat.',
    maintenance: '<strong>Priority:</strong> Match calories to expenditure. Focus on food quality and consistent meal timing over strict tracking.',
    beginner:    '<strong>Priority:</strong> Don\'t overthink it. Eat mostly whole foods, hit your protein, and avoid liquid calories. Consistency beats perfection.',
  },
  recovery: {
    muscle:      '<strong>Priority:</strong> Sleep 8–9 hours. Growth hormone peaks during deep sleep — this is when your muscles actually repair and grow.',
    fatloss:     '<strong>Priority:</strong> Sleep deprivation raises ghrelin (hunger hormone) and cortisol. Poor sleep = more cravings + less fat burning.',
    maintenance: '<strong>Priority:</strong> Maintain a consistent sleep schedule. Your body performs best when recovery patterns are predictable.',
    beginner:    '<strong>Priority:</strong> Your body is adapting to new stress. You need MORE recovery than advanced athletes, not less. Rest is not weakness.',
  },
  exercise: {
    muscle:      '<strong>Priority:</strong> Train each muscle 2x per week with progressive overload. Volume and intensity matter more than session length.',
    fatloss:     '<strong>Priority:</strong> Strength training preserves muscle in a deficit. Combine with cardio for maximum calorie burn. Don\'t just do cardio.',
    maintenance: '<strong>Priority:</strong> Maintain your training frequency. Consistency is more important than new programs when at maintenance.',
    beginner:    '<strong>Priority:</strong> Full body 3x per week. Master form before adding weight. Progress will come fast in your first 3 months — trust the process.',
  },
};

const GUIDES_DATA = [
  {
    id: 'nutrition',
    icon: '🥗',
    title: 'NUTRITION',
    sub: 'Fuel your body right — for your specific goal',
    sections: {
      muscle: [
        { title: 'Calorie Surplus & Macros', pts: [
          'Eat 200–400 kcal above your maintenance level. More than this adds unnecessary fat.',
          'Protein: 1.6–2g per kg bodyweight daily. Split across 3–4 meals.',
          'Carbohydrates are your energy currency. Prioritise around training: before and after.',
          'Fats: 0.8–1g per kg. Don\'t go lower — hormones including testosterone need dietary fat.',
          'Track with a phone app for 2 weeks. Awareness alone changes habits significantly.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Best Kenyan Protein Sources', pts: [
          'Eggs: cheapest complete protein. 3 eggs = 18g protein. Eat daily.',
          'Beef: high in creatine and zinc. Best post-workout meal when affordable.',
          'Fish (tilapia, dagaa): lean, affordable, packed with protein and omega-3.',
          'Beans & lentils: combine with rice or ugali for a complete amino acid profile.',
          'Milk (fresh or powder): cheap whey alternative. 500ml = 17g protein.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Carbs for Performance', pts: [
          'Sweet potato: slow digesting, rich in potassium. Best pre-workout carb.',
          'Ugali (maize meal): fast energy. Ideal immediately post-workout.',
          'Brown rice and oats: sustained energy for long training days.',
          'Fruits (banana, mango): natural sugars for quick pre-session energy.',
          'Avoid refined carbs at night unless it is directly post-workout.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Meal Timing', pts: [
          'Pre-workout (60–90 min before): carbs + moderate protein. No heavy fats.',
          'Post-workout (within 60 min): protein + fast carbs to start recovery.',
          'Spread protein across all meals. 20–40g per meal is optimal for muscle synthesis.',
          'Don\'t train fasted for muscle gain — performance and muscle breakdown suffer.',
          'Last meal: casein-rich foods (milk, eggs, cheese) to feed muscles overnight.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Hydration & Extras', pts: [
          'Minimum 3 litres of water daily. Add 500ml per hour of training.',
          'Add salt to meals and water on heavy training days to replace electrolytes.',
          'Creatine monohydrate: 3–5g daily. The single most effective supplement available.',
          'Black coffee pre-workout: free performance boost. No fancy pre-workout needed.',
          'Alcohol kills testosterone, disrupts sleep, and impairs protein synthesis. Minimise it.',
        ]},
      ],
      fatloss: [
        { title: 'Calorie Deficit Done Right', pts: [
          'Target 300–500 kcal below maintenance. Bigger deficits cause muscle loss and burnout.',
          'Weigh yourself weekly, not daily. Daily weight fluctuates by 1–2kg due to water and food.',
          'If weight stalls for 2+ weeks, reduce calories by 100–150 kcal or add 20 min cardio.',
          'Do not drop below 1,500 kcal (men) or 1,200 kcal (women) without medical guidance.',
          'Diet breaks: one week at maintenance every 6–8 weeks resets hormones and motivation.',
        ]},
        { title: 'High-Protein Eating for Fat Loss', pts: [
          'High protein (1.8–2.2g/kg) preserves muscle while in a calorie deficit.',
          'Protein is the most filling macronutrient — it reduces hunger hormones naturally.',
          'Start every meal with protein. It controls appetite and prevents overeating carbs.',
          'Eggs, chicken, fish, beans, and milk are your go-to affordable protein sources.',
          'Greek yoghurt and cottage cheese are excellent high-protein, low-calorie snacks.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Cutting Calories Smartly', pts: [
          'Cut liquid calories first. Sodas, juice, and chai with lots of sugar add up fast.',
          'Reduce cooking oil. Fats are 9 kcal/g vs 4 kcal/g for protein and carbs.',
          'Eat whole fruits instead of juice. The fibre keeps you full and slows sugar absorption.',
          'Smaller plates genuinely work. Portion perception affects satiety psychologically.',
          'Eat slowly. It takes 15–20 minutes for the fullness signal to reach your brain.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Foods That Help Fat Loss', pts: [
          'Sukuma wiki, spinach, and cabbage: very low calorie, high fibre and micronutrients.',
          'Eggs: high protein, moderate fat, very filling. Perfect fat-loss food.',
          'Avocado: healthy fats that suppress hunger. One half per meal is enough.',
          'Black coffee and green tea: suppress appetite and boost metabolism slightly.',
          'Legumes (beans, lentils): high fibre + protein = keeps you full for hours cheaply.',
        ]},
        { title: 'What to Reduce or Avoid', pts: [
          'Ultra-processed foods: mandazi, crisps, biscuits. Empty calories that do not fill you.',
          'White bread and white rice in large quantities: fast digesting, spike insulin quickly.',
          'Alcohol: 7 kcal/gram, zero nutrition, lowers inhibitions making overeating likely.',
          'Skip eating out frequently — restaurant and fast food portions are calorie bombs.',
          'Late-night snacking: it is rarely hunger. Brush teeth at 9pm to signal the kitchen is closed.',
        ]},
      ],
      maintenance: [
        { title: 'Finding Your Maintenance Calories', pts: [
          'Track food for 2 weeks while weight stays the same — that is your maintenance.',
          'Rough estimate: bodyweight (kg) × 33 kcal = maintenance for moderately active people.',
          'Adjust by 100–150 kcal every 2 weeks based on weight trend.',
          'Maintenance is a range, not a fixed number. It shifts with activity, stress, and season.',
          'You can be more relaxed at maintenance — focus on food quality over strict tracking.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Balanced Macros', pts: [
          'Protein: 1.2–1.6g/kg bodyweight. Enough to maintain muscle without obsessing.',
          'Carbs: make up the bulk of your calories. Eat what your activity level demands.',
          'Fats: 25–35% of total calories for hormonal health and brain function.',
          'Don\'t over-restrict any macronutrient at maintenance. Balance is sustainable.',
          'Prioritise food variety — different colours on the plate means different nutrients.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Long-Term Sustainable Habits', pts: [
          '80/20 rule: eat well 80% of the time. 20% flexibility keeps you sane long-term.',
          'Cook most meals at home. Restaurant food is hard to track and typically calorie-dense.',
          'Meal prep 2–3 days at a time. Preparation removes daily decision fatigue.',
          'Learn 5–6 go-to healthy meals you enjoy. Repetition is not boring — it is efficient.',
          'Never restrict so hard that you binge. Steady beats extreme every single time.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Micronutrients & Whole Foods', pts: [
          'Eat a variety of vegetables daily. Sukuma, tomatoes, carrots, onions at minimum.',
          'Include fruits 1–2 times daily. Mangoes, bananas, pawpaw are accessible and nutritious.',
          'Whole grains over refined. Brown ugali, brown rice, whole wheat bread where possible.',
          'Fermented foods (fermented milk, yoghurt) support gut health and immunity.',
          'Sun exposure + vitamin D foods (eggs, fatty fish) combat the Kenyan indoor lifestyle.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Eating Out Without Ruining Progress', pts: [
          'Choose protein + vegetable combinations when eating out. Avoid fried everything.',
          'Request sauces on the side. Most restaurant calories hide in dressings and sauces.',
          'Drink water before the meal. Reduces overeating by 20% on average.',
          'Don\'t arrive at restaurants starving — you will make poor choices.',
          'One indulgent meal per week does not break progress. Consistency wins over months.',
        ]},
      ],
      beginner: [
        { title: 'Keep It Dead Simple', pts: [
          'Eat mostly whole, unprocessed foods. If it comes in a packet with 20 ingredients, eat less of it.',
          'Hit your protein target every day. Everything else can come later.',
          'Rough daily protein: bodyweight in kg = grams of protein. 65kg = 65g protein minimum.',
          'Three meals per day is fine. You do not need 6 meals or special timing to start.',
          'Stop drinking calories. Switch soda, juice, and chai with lots of sugar to water first.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Easy Affordable Kenyan Meals', pts: [
          'Breakfast: 3 eggs scrambled + 2 slices whole bread + black tea without sugar.',
          'Lunch: ugali + beans + sukuma wiki. Balanced, cheap, high protein and fibre.',
          'Dinner: brown rice + tilapia or chicken + tomato-onion salad.',
          'Snacks: banana, boiled egg, groundnuts, or plain yoghurt.',
          'These four meals alone will out-perform most "diet plans" for beginners.',
        ]},
        { title: 'What to Stop Doing Immediately', pts: [
          'Stop skipping breakfast — it leads to overeating later and energy crashes.',
          'Stop drinking sodas daily. Replace with water. This alone can shift 2–3kg in a month.',
          'Stop eating until uncomfortably full. Eat to 80% full and wait 15 minutes.',
          'Stop buying supplements before mastering basic food habits.',
          'Stop following extreme diets. Sustainable beats drastic every single time.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Understanding Calories Simply', pts: [
          'Calories are energy. Eat more than you burn = gain weight. Eat less = lose weight.',
          'You do not need to count every calorie as a beginner — just be aware of portions.',
          'Protein and vegetables fill you up on fewer calories. Prioritise both.',
          'Fat does not make you fat. Excess calories do. Avocado and groundnuts are fine.',
          'Carbs are not bad. White ugali eaten in huge amounts without activity — that is the issue.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Building the Habit', pts: [
          'Plan meals the night before. Decision fatigue leads to bad choices at lunchtime.',
          'One small positive change per week. Don\'t overhaul everything on day one.',
          'Do not aim for perfection. Missing one good meal does not ruin your progress.',
          'Find one healthy meal you genuinely enjoy and eat it regularly.',
          'Track your water intake for one week. Most people are chronically dehydrated without knowing.',
        ]},
      ],
    },
  },
  {
    id: 'recovery',
    icon: '😴',
    title: 'RECOVERY & REST',
    sub: 'When your muscles actually grow — optimise it',
    sections: {
      muscle: [
        { title: 'Sleep — The Most Anabolic Tool', pts: [
          'Aim for 8–9 hours. Growth hormone is released primarily during deep sleep stages 3 & 4.',
          'Consistent sleep and wake times matter more than total hours alone.',
          'Avoid screens 1 hour before bed. Blue light suppresses melatonin by up to 50%.',
          'Sleep in a cool (16–19°C), dark room. Temperature drop signals the brain to sleep.',
          'Even one night of 5–6 hours reduces testosterone by 10–15%. Sleep is not optional.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Training Frequency & Rest Days', pts: [
          'Each muscle group needs 48–72 hours to recover before training again.',
          'Take at least 1–2 full rest days per week. Active rest (light walk) is ideal.',
          'Back-to-back sessions on the same muscle group = overtraining, not dedication.',
          'If you are always sore, always tired, or losing strength — you are underrecovering.',
          'More volume only works if you can recover from it. Quality over quantity.',
        ]},
        { title: 'Nutrition for Recovery', pts: [
          'Post-workout: 30–40g protein within 60 minutes. Muscle protein synthesis window is open.',
